"Kubernetes" - another way to write the same greek word as "Cybernetics" - "Feedback Loops" Terms: - "Cluster" - machines in your cluter are called "Nodes" - Two types of nodes: - Control Plane - those machines that take care of the cluster - API - database (etcd) - scheduler - it scans the database for our "desired state" - it constantly uses a feedback loop that monitors the "actual state" against our "desired state" - and will fix it if it varies. - Worker Nodes - the ones that run our code
